This paper focuses on the development of generative models for automatic knowledge base construction, specifically for commonsense knowledge graphs. This involves natural language processing, machine learning, and knowledge representation, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pre-trained language models and transfer learning, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
